<LegalLayout
  title="Accuracy Disclaimer"
  description="Why travel conditions change, and how ADVNTR Road handles verification and updates."
  canonicalPath="/accuracy-disclaimer"
>
  <p>
    Every ADVNTR Road guide is verified against official park, agency, and reservation
    sources as of its printed "verified" date. After that date, conditions change: fees
    change, reservation systems change, roads close, campgrounds flood out, businesses
    close, and weather rewrites a season's plans.
  </p>
  <p>
    Always confirm current conditions — fees, permits, closures, road status, and business
    hours — directly with the official source (NPS.gov, Recreation.gov, or the relevant
    state agency) before you travel. Treat every guide as a strong starting point, not a
    live feed.
  </p>
  <h2>How we handle updates</h2>
  <p>
    The Trailhead, our weekly national park intel column, is one of the ways we catch
    conditions that affect a published guide. When a change is significant enough to
    matter, it's logged internally and reflected in the guide's next edition.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
